<subSubSection id="B8CC65052C06FFBAF7F9A6C09BEE6EE5" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="F069368E2C06FFBAF7F9A6C09BEE6EE5" blockId="3.[2070,2665,300,718]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
<taxonomicName id="37D64D0D2C06FFBAF7F9A6C09A6B6D91" authorityName="Coues" authorityYear="1875" box="[2073,2151,409,442]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Zapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Zapus</taxonomicName>
apparently arose in Asia from an 
<taxonomicName id="37D64D0D2C06FFBAF5DFA6C09A6D6DC9" authorityName="Preble" authorityYear="1899" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Eozapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Eozapus</taxonomicName>
ancestor that had moved across the Bering Strait into North America and gave rise to Z. rinkeri (the first known 
<taxonomicName id="37D64D0D2C06FFBAF5E4A54D98546E1A" authorityName="Coues" authorityYear="1875" box="[2564,2648,532,561]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Zapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Zapus</taxonomicName>
), then Z. burti and 
<taxonomicName id="37D64D0D2C06FFBAF6F2A56E9BB56E73" baseAuthorityName="Zimmermann" baseAuthorityYear="1780" box="[2322,2489,567,600]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Zapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hudsonius">Z. hudsonius</taxonomicName>
, which gave rise to 
<taxonomicName id="37D64D0D2C06FFBAF79FA53A9B246EAB" authorityName="Preble" authorityYear="1899" box="[2175,2344,611,640]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Napaeozapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Napaeozapus</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="37D64D0D2C06FFBAF6DDA53A9B876EAB" authorityName="Coues" authorityYear="1875" box="[2365,2443,611,640]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Zapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Zapus</taxonomicName>
burti may then have given rise to 
<taxonomicName id="37D64D0D2C06FFBAF6FCA5DF9BB06E8C" authorityName="Rhoads" authorityYear="1895" box="[2332,2492,646,679]" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Zapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="trinotatus">Z. trinotatus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="37D64D0D2C06FFBAF5E7A5DF9A466EE5" authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1893" class="Mammalia" family="Dipodidae" genus="Zapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="princeps">Z. princeps</taxonomicName>
. Four subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
